quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  43,48,"We did not show them a sign but it was greater than the other, and We visited on them punishment so that they might come back"
  43,49,"They would say, ‘O magician! Invoke your Lord for us by the covenant He has made with you [to remove this scourge]. We will indeed be guided [when it is removed].’"
  43,50,"But when We lifted the punishment from them, behold, they would break their pledge"
  43,51,"And Pharaoh proclaimed to his people, saying, ‘O my people! Do not the kingdom of Egypt and these rivers that run at my feet belong to me? Do you not perceive"
  43,52,Am I not better than this wretch who cannot even speak clearly
  43,53,"Why no bracelets of gold have been thrown to him, nor any angels accompany him as escorts?’"
  43,54,"Thus did he mislead his people and they obeyed him. Indeed, they were a transgressing lot"
  43,55,"So when they roused Our wrath, We took vengeance on them and drowned them all"
  43,56,Thus We made them the vanguard and an example for posterity
  43,57,"When the Son of Mary was cited as an example, behold, your people raise an outcry"
  43,58,"They say, ‘Are our gods better or he?’ They cite him to you only for the sake of contention. Indeed, they are a contentious lot"
  43,59,He was just a servant whom We had blessed and made an exemplar for the Children of Israel
  43,60,"Had We wished We would have set angels in your stead to be [your] successors on the earth"